# CroqTile Slides — reveal.js

## Structure
- Each deck lives in `decks/<name>/index.html`
- Build outputs go to `decks/<name>/dist/`
- Theme CSS in `themes/croqtile-dark.css`
- Shared assets in `assets/images/`

## Slide Syntax
- Each slide is a `<section>` inside `<div class="slides">`
- Use `class="lead"` for centered title/closing slides
- Use `class="chapter"` for chapter divider slides
- Use `<div class="split">` for two-column layouts

## Code Blocks
- Use `<div class="editor-block" data-lang="choreo" data-file="kernel.co" data-badge="CROQTILE">` for single code blocks with IDE chrome
- Use `<div class="editor-showcase" data-tabs='[...]'>` for tabbed code comparison
- Supported languages: `choreo`, `cpp`, `cuda`
- The custom syntax highlighter runs client-side in vanilla JS

## Build
- `npm run build` — builds all decks (Node.js, cross-platform)
- `npm run build:html` — HTML only
- `npm run dev` — local preview server (Node.js)
- `python3 scripts/build.py` — builds all decks (Python, Linux/macOS)
- `python3 scripts/build.py <deck-name>` — build specific deck

## Style
- Font: Inter + JetBrains Mono
- Accent: mint green (#22c55e / #16a34a)
- Keep slides concise: 6-8 bullets max
- Code blocks should use editor-block for visual consistency
